2 Line runs between South Bellevue Station and Downtown Redmond Station seven days a week

summary.value: 1 Line has resumed regular service. Please expect delays as service recovers.

description.value:
Between Feb. 14 and March 27, passengers can board 2 Line trains between Lynnwood and International District/Chinatown. All passengers must exit at International District/Chinatown and board 1 Line trains to travel further south during final testing. 

- Pay attention to train head signs. 
- Passengers traveling south of downtown Seattle must board 1 Line trains. 
- Passengers traveling between Lynnwood and International District/Chinatown can board 1 Line or 2 Line trains. 
- All passengers MUST exit 2 Line trains at International District/Chinatown, starting Feb.14. 
- Airport travelers should wait for 1 Line trains to avoid transferring. 

2 Line service between Redmond and Lynnwood begins March 28.

summary.value: 2 Line trains have begun service between Lynnwood and International District/Chinatown. Passengers traveling south of International District/Chinatown must board 1 Line trains.
